         <notesStmt>
            <note>Lacuna after folio 52. Folios 113-118 originally belonged to another manuscript of about the same date. Folios 111, 112, 119-124 are a recent addition. Water-damaged.</note>
            <note>Maimon ben Se῾adya᾿ ben Mosheh Al-Musa᾿i (patron): inscribed, folio 110v.Folios 111-112: a calendar for the 286th and 287th cycle, followed by the series of prognostications based on the date of the teḳufot.Folios 113-118: originally a part of another manuscript: several poetical pieces and additional blessings.Folios 119r-123r: originally belonging to a different manuscript of approximately 18th century: additional prayers.Folios 122v-123r: tiḳunim.Folios 123v-124r: a table with a 292th cycle.Folio 2r: partly illegible piece similar to Kol nidre.Folio 2v: a poetical piece.Folio 3r: three additional prayers.Folio 4r: an additional prayer and the beginning of Kol nidre.
								Zekhariah ben Daṿid: inscribed with his name in a note, folio 1v.
								Avraham ben Shalom: inscribed, folio 2r.Folio 124r: two records of sale, dated 1797 and 1811 respectively.</note>
            <note type="relatedResource">
								Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.
							</note>
